{"id":"lrn_65888a9620f16ca29bc5","repository_id":"repo_ivan-learnings","kind":"repo_convention","statement":"GPT-4o-mini reformats the ticket into a structured prompt while the original is stored in the DB","status":"active","evidence_ids":["ev_a9ad14c34cb9f83cfb08"],"tags":["cli"],"created_at":"2026-03-11T18:06:14.301Z","updated_at":"2026-03-11T18:06:14.301Z","source_type":"github_pr_discourse","title":"GPT-4o-mini reformats the ticket into a structured prompt while the o...","rationale":"PR 15: Feature/prompt rewriting Adds an optional --rewrite-prompt step that cleans up noisy tickets (Slack threads, metadata, boilerplate) before sending them to Claude Code. GPT-4o-mini reformats the ticket into a structured prompt while the original is stored in the DB. Also fixes a CLI bug where --disallowed-tools could accidentally consume the task prompt during argument parsing. Verify Build: npm run build npm link 1. ivan --rewrite-prompt \"Add a loading spinner\" → see \"🔄 Rewriting prompt...\" before Claude runs 2. ivan \"some task\" --rewrite-prompt → same, flag order shouldn't matter 3. ivan --rewrite-prompt → prompts interactively, doesn't crash 4. ivan \"some task\" → no rewriting, unchanged behaviour Verify DB after any rewrite run: sqlite3 ~/.ivan/db.sqlite \"SELECT description, original description FROM tasks ORDER BY uuid DESC LIMIT 1;\" description = rewritten · original description = raw input Changed files: - src/database/migrations/014 add original description column.ts - src/database/migrations/index.ts - src/database/types.ts - src/index.ts - src/services/claude-cli-executor.ts - src/services/job-manager.ts - src/services/openai-service.ts - src/services/prompt-rewriter.ts - src/services/task-executor.ts - src/types/non-interactive-config.ts","applicability":"Use this in this repository’s CLI, Claude Code, hook, and automation paths.","confidence":0.6,"embedding":[0,0,0.021879166839686815,0,0.13127500103812087,-0.1531541678778077,0,-0.04375833367937363,0,-0.0